@comment ** 3.5 >>IF Directive                                              **
@comment *********************************************************************
@page
@newsection{3.5,>>IF}
@diagram{CDF >>IF Directive,CDF-IF,CDF-IF,None}
@diagram{CDF-Conditional-Expression,CDF-Cond-Expr,CDF-Cond-Expr,None}
@diagram{CDF-RelOp,CDF-RelOp,CDF-RelOp,None}@p The @directive{>>IF} causes the GnuCOBOL compiler to process or ignore COBOL source statements, CDF text-manipulation statements and/or CDF directives depending upon the value of one or more conditional expressions based upon CDF variables.
@enumerate
@p @item The reserved words @syntax{IS}, @syntax{THAN} and @syntax{TO} are optional and may be included, or not, at the discretion of the programmer.  The presence or absence of these words has no effect upon the program.
@p @item Each @syntax{>>IF} directive must be terminated by an @syntaxidx{>>END-IF} directive.
@p @item There may be any number of @syntaxidx{>>ELIF} clauses following an @syntax{>>IF}, including zero.
@p @item There may no more than one @syntaxidx{>>ELSE} clause following an @syntax{>>IF}.  When @syntax{>>ELSE} is used, it must follow the @syntax{>>IF} and all @syntax{>>ELIF} clauses.
@p @item Only one of the @clause{Program-Source-Lines-n} block of statements that lie within the scope of the @syntax{>>IF}-@syntax{>>END-IF} may be processed by the compiler.  Which one (if any) that gets processed will be decided as follows:
@enumerate A
@p @item Each @clause{CDF-Conditional-Expression-n} will be evaluated, in turn, in the sequence in which they are coded in the >>IF statement and any @syntax{>>ELIF} clauses that may be present until one evaluates to TRUE.  Once one of them evaluates to TRUE, the @clause{Program-Source-Lines-n} block of code that corresponds to the TRUE @clause{CDF-Conditional-Expression-n} will be one that is processed.  All others within the @syntax{>>IF}-@syntax{>>END-IF} scope will be ignored.
@p @item If no @clause{CDF-Conditional-Expression} evaluates to TRUE, and there is an @syntax{>>ELSE} clause, the @clause{Program-Source-Lines-3} block of statements following the @syntax{>>ELSE} clause will be processed by the compiler and all others within the @syntax{>>IF}-@syntax{>>END-IF} scope will be ignored.
@p @item If no @clause{CDF-Conditional-Expression-n} evaluates to TRUE and there is no @syntax{>>ELSE} clause, then none of the @clause{Program-Source-Lines-n} block of statements within the @syntax{>>IF}-@syntax{>>END-IF} scope will be processed by the compiler.
@p @item If the @term{Program-Source-Lines-n}> statement block selected for processing is empty, no error results --- there will just be no code generated from the @syntax{>>IF}-@syntax{>>END-IF} structure.
@end enumerate
@item A @clause{Program-Source-Lines-n} block may contain any valid COBOL or CDF code.
@p @item The following points pertain to any @clause{CDF-Conditional-Expression-n}:
@enumerate A
@p @item The @syntaxidx{DEFINED} option tests for whether @term{cdf-variable-1} has been defined, but not yet assigned a value (@syntax{>>DEFINE @dots{} OFF}); use the @syntax{NOT} option to test for the variable not being defined.
@p @item The @syntaxidx{SET} option tests for whether @term{cdf-variable-1} has been given a value, either via a @syntax{>>SET} statement or via a @syntax{>>DEFINE} without the @syntax{OFF} option.
@p @item Two CDF variables, two literals or a single CDF variable and a single literal may be compared against each other using a relational operator.  Unlike the standard GnuCOBOL @statementref{IF}, multiple comparisons cannot be "AND"ed or "OR"ed together; you may nest a second @syntax{>>IF} inside the first, however, to simulate an "AND" and an "OR" may be simulated via the @syntax{>>ELIF} option.
@p @item The @syntax{<>} symbol stands for @syntax{NOT EQUAL TO}.
@end enumerate
@end enumerate
