@comment ** 3.6 >>SET Directive                                             **
@comment *********************************************************************
@page
@newsection{3.6,>>SET}
@diagram{CDF >>SET Directive,CDF-SET,CDF-SET,None}@p The @directive{>>SET} provides an alternate means of performing the actions of the @syntax{>>DEFINE} and @syntax{>>SOURCE} directives, as well as a means of controlling the compiler's @switchidx{-free}, @switchidx{-fixed} and @switchidx{-ffold-copy} from within program source code.
@enumerate
@p @item The reserved word @syntax{AS} is optional (only on the @syntax{SOURCEFORMAT} and @syntax{FOLDCOPYNAME} clauses) and may be included, or not, at the discretion of the programmer.  The presence or absence of this word has no effect upon the program.
@p @item CDF variables defined in this way become undefined once an @syntax{END PROGRAM} or @syntax{END FUNCTION} directive is encountered in the input source.
@p @item The @syntaxidx{FOLDCOPYNAME} option provides the equivalent of specifying the compiler @switch{-ffold-copy=xxx}, where "xxx" is either @syntaxidx{UPPER} or @syntaxidx{LOWER}.
@p @item The @syntaxidx{NOFOLDCOPYNAME} option turns off the effect of either the @syntax{>>SET FOLDCOPYNAME} statement or the compiler @switch{-ffold-copy=xxx}.
@p @item If the @syntaxidx{CONSTANT} option is used, @term{literal-1} must also be used.  This option provides another means of defining constants that may be used anywhere in the program that a literal could be specified.
@p @item The remaining options of the @directive{>>SET} provide equivalent functionality to the @syntax{>>DEFINE} and @syntax{>>SOURCE} directives, as follows:
@enumerate A
@p @item @syntax{>>SET @term{cdf-variable-1}} @equiv{} @syntax{>>DEFINE @term{cdf-variable-1} AS OFF}
@p @item @syntax{>>SET @term{cdf-variable-1} AS @term{literal-1}} @equiv{} @syntax{>>DEFINE @term{cdf-variable-1} AS @term{literal-1}}
@p @item @syntax{>>SET CONSTANT @term{cdf-variable-1} @term{literal-1}} @equiv{} @syntax{>>DEFINE CONSTANT @term{cdf-variable-1} @term{literal-1}}
@p @item @syntax{>>SET SOURCEFORMAT AS FIXED} @equiv{} @syntax{>>SOURCE FORMAT IS FIXED}
@p @item @syntax{>>SET SOURCEFORMAT AS FREE} @equiv{} @syntax{>>SOURCE FORMAT IS FREE}
@end enumerate
@end enumerate
